reviews.headline: Jury is still out
reviews.comments:
I haven't really used Bare Minerals (except for their eye shadows) since like 2011 when I realized one of the ingredients in their loose powder bothered my skin. However, the ads kept popping up in my feed, so I decided to give them another try. 
Pros: doesn't settle into my fine lines, doesn't seem to bother my skin, looks natural, doesn't make me oily
Cons: definitely doesn't last all day, even with a setting spray 

I've worn it over my liquid Est√©e Lauder foundation and on its own. Either way, I like the finish effect. I'm 45, so I've tried every brand under the sun. It's not a holy grail product for me, but it's pretty good.

reviews.headline: This is it!!!!
reviews.comments:
I've used BareMinerals off and on for over 20 years and have always loved the compact makeup. Recently, I decided to return to the brand because I have extremely sensitive skin‚Äîand drugstore makeup had been causing awful breakouts, irritation, redness, and itching.

When I saw the new pressed powder on display in-store, I grabbed it immediately‚Äîand I'm so glad I did. After just two days of use, my skin completely cleared up. No more redness, bumps, or irritation. HALLELUJAH!

Thank you, BareMinerals, for making a clean, skin-loving product that us sensitive girlies can actually wear with confidence. üíñ

faceoff_positive.comments:
Thanks, bareMinerals for the free sample of Original Talc-Free Pressed Powder Foundation Mineral SPF 15 in Fairly Light 03 in exchange for my review through BzzAgent's sampling program! When I opened the package, I was struck by the beauty of the sleek and attractive compact! The compact design is not only aesthetically pleasing, but also practical. It comes with a sponge for convenient application. I was very impressed by the quality of the product when I applied it. I use a powder brush to apply it all over my face, neck, and decolletage, and the sponge for under my eyes in the morning (also for touch-ups throughout the day). 
The formula blends effortlessly for a flawless, luminous finish. The consistency is light yet offers buildable coverage that conceals imperfections while allowing my skin to breathe. It provides a nice, natural finish that enhances my complexion without looking cakey. The subtle sheen adds a healthy, youthful appearance that I love. It gives my face a radiant glow, making it look like my own skin, but better! I have sensitive skin, so I appreciate the gentle ingredients that don't cause any irritation or breakouts. It's also cruelty-free, making it a great choice for people with delicate skin and tender hearts. Compared to other powder foundations I've tried, it stands out for its quality, ease of use, and skin-friendly formula. 
This foundation is perfect for everyday wear and special occasions. After a solid week of daily use, it has proven to be a reliable, high-quality product that delivers a beautiful, natural finish. The SPF 15 is a huge bonus, providing sun protection while keeping my skin looking its best. The foundation has become a staple in my makeup routine, so I plan to purchase it in the future. I highly recommend this fantastic product to anyone looking for a reliable, effective foundation that's gentle on sensitive skin and offers protection from the sun and a beautiful finish!
faceoff_positive.headline: Adds a radiant glow - like my own skin, but better!

faceoff_negative.comments:
I recently received the Talc Free Powder Foundation with SPF 15 in the shade Fairly Light, and I was excited to try it out, especially since finding the right color can be a challenge. The shade was indeed a perfect match for my skin tone, which is always a win. However, my experience with the product hasn't been entirely positive. 

Once applied, I noticed that it tended to settle into my pores and fine lines, which left my complexion looking somewhat uneven. I had hoped for a smoother, more flawless finish, but instead, it seemed to accentuate areas I would rather downplay. Although the SPF 15 is a nice addition for sun protection, the overall texture of the foundation didn't meet my expectations. I believe that with some tweaks to the formula or application method, it could be a great product, but for now, I'm left feeling a bit disappointed.llenge.
